    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, but i've noticed some people in the industry feel like \"intentional\" or \"neatly shaped\" can be a bit of a code word. like, for some of my clients with natural black hair, they feel like if they don't go with a smooth or straightened look, they're seen as less professional or \"distracting\" in the boardroom. do you think there's a way to say that certain more \"unstructured\" natural styles might be perceived as less authoritative compared to more traditional, sleek looks?",
